  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 300 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "Season the lamb shoulder with salt and black pepper.",
    "Heat the olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.",
    "Sear the lamb shoulder until browned on all sides, then set aside.",
    "Add the chopped onions and leeks to the pot and cook until softened.",
    "Add the garlic, rosemary, and celery root to the pot and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the red wine vinegar, potatoes, and infuse oil to the pot.",
    "Return the lamb shoulder to the pot and transfer to the preheated oven.",
    "Bake for 2 hours, or until the lamb is tender and the sauce is thickened.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with fresh rosemary and celery leaves."
